svg.desc: Using two maps of Germany, the diagram shows the number of residents per county looked after by one general specialist in 2010 and 2016. There are major regional differences. In 2016, the figures ranged from 440 residents per general specialist in Heidelberg to 2,270 in Gifhorn. When it comes to general specialists, care is concentrated in cities, whereby the general specialist also look after patients from the surrounding region. General specialists include eye specialists, surgeons, gynaecologists, dermatologists, ear, nose and throat specialists, neurologists, orthopaedists, psychotherapists, urologists and paediatricians.

div.p:
Source: National Association of Statutory Health Insurance Physicians, special analysis. Data for general practitioners December 31, 2016; Source: Federal Registry of Physicians.
